text: Julian Christopher Jenner (born 28 February 1984) is a Dutch professional footballer who plays as a winger. He is currently clubless. His former teams are AZ Alkmaar and NAC Breda. Jenner is nicknamed "The Scissor Kid" after his skills and stepovers, and is well known for his pace. On 14 June 2008, it was announced that Jenner signed a contract with Vitesse Arnhem, together with teammate Rogier Molhoek. In January 2010, Jenner went on loan to Rot-Weiss Ahlen until the end of the season. ==International career== In 2007, Jenner was called up by Jong Oranje coach Foppe de Haan to be part of his squad for the 2007 UEFA European Under-21 Football Championship held in the Netherlands. Jenner participated in both of their first round group matches against Israel (1–0 win) and Portugal (2–1 win) to secure a semi final spot and to qualify for the 2008 Summer Olympics. Later the final was reached with a 1–1, 13–12 win after a penalty shootout with 32 penalty kicks taken against England.
